{
  "texts": [
    "Then we extend the line from the parent cluster centroid C p to C s ub and calculate the intersection point of the extended line and the parent border.",
    "The intersection point is used to position the sub-cluster label, resulting in a radial layout, as shown in Figure 6-d.",
    "The generalizability of the concave hull algorithm makes our labeling position calculation applicable to any curve used for the SFC layout.",
    "The HINTs system consists of three main views: Cluster View, Document View, and Analysis View.",
    "Below, we describe the views, visualizations, and interactions, and how they assist the exploration and reorganization of a corpus."
  ]
